  "suggestion": "[attribution-theory+clinical-psychology+motivation+social-cognition] IMPLEMENT NOW вҖ” Causal Attribution Spine (Weiner 1985). The model currently predicts which need is violated but not *why the person thinks it happened*. Attribution determines the emotion that follows: the same outcome (failure) produces shame, anger, or sadness depending on locus Г— stability Г— controllability. Add a 3-axis attribution computation after free-energy need selection: (1) locus = internal if `personalRelevance > 0.6 && person.traits.neuroticism > 0.5` else external; (2) stability = stable if `person.history?.length >= 2 && same rootCause appeared before` else unstable; (3) controllability = controllable if dominant need is `achievement` or `autonomy`, uncontrollable otherwise. Then map the 2Ві cell to a canonical emotion: {internal,stable,uncontrollableвҶ’shame/depression}, {internal,unstable,controllableвҶ’guiltвҶ’adaptive coping}, {external,stable,uncontrollableвҶ’helplessness}, {external,unstable,uncontrollableвҶ’surprise/luck}, {external,controllableвҶ’anger at other}. This replaces the current flat emotion lookup and directly covers the psychopathology and motivation benchmark domains where locus matters most. вҖ” Math: Attribution вҲҲ {I,E} Г— {S,U} Г— {C,U} вҶ’ 8-cell lookup вҶ’ (emotion, coping_style, motivation_direction). Locus = sigmoid(personalRelevance Г— neuroticism вҲ’ 0.5). Stability = I[historyMatch]. Controllability = I[need вҲҲ {achievement, autonomy}].; [dynamical-systems+statistical-physics+psychopathology+clinical-psychology] Phase Transition Thresholds вҖ” Behavioral Criticality. Human behavior does not change linearly: it undergoes sudden qualitative phase transitions like matter (iceвҶ’waterвҶ’steam). The existing model interpolates smoothly, missing the all-or-nothing quality of snapping, falling in love, hitting rock bottom, or entering flow. Add a per-domain critical threshold П„_d on the dominant need's free energy F*. Below П„: normal regulatory response (current behavior). At П„: order parameter flips вҖ” the system jumps to a qualitatively different attractor: high-F safety вҶ’ freeze/dissociation (not just anxiety); high-F belonging вҶ’ fusion/enmeshment (not just closeness); high-F esteem вҶ’ grandiosity or collapse (not just defensiveness). Person parameter: `brittleness = neuroticism Г— (1 - conscientiousness)` scales how close П„ is to baseline F. Math: if F* > П„_d Г— (1 + resilience), output behavior = phaseState[domain] else normal. This explains borderline PD (hair-trigger transitions), flow (cognitive load crosses threshold into absorption), and conversion disorder (shutdown past threshold). вҖ” Math: Order parameter ПҶ = tanh((F* вҲ’ П„) / Оө) where Оө = person.brittleness. If ПҶ > 0.8: jump to high-energy attractor behavior. П„_d is domain-calibrated: psychopathology П„ вүҲ 0.6, decision П„ вүҲ 0.8, social П„ вүҲ 0.7. Resilience = conscientiousness Г— (1 вҲ’ neuroticism) raises П„.; [physics+social-psychology+neuroscience+music-theory] Social Entrainment Oscillator вҖ” Coupling & Resonance. The model treats social context as a setting flag but ignores the dynamical coupling between people. From physics: coupled oscillators synchronize (entrainment). In humans: emotional contagion, conformity, and groupthink are entrainment phenomena. Model each person as an oscillator with natural frequency Пү (baseline arousal rhythm) and coupling strength Оә (extraversion Г— agreeableness). Social stimulus = forcing oscillation at frequency Пү_group. Resonance condition: |Пү_person вҲ’ Пү_group| < Оҙ вҶ’ amplification вҶ’ emotion intensified Г— (1 + Оә). Anti-resonance: |Пү_person вҲ’ Пү_group| > Оҙ вҶ’ interference вҶ’ person feels drained/alienated. Implement: in social domain, multiply the winning need's free energy by resonanceFactor = 1 + Оә Г— exp(вҲ’|arousal вҲ’ groupArousal|ВІ / 2ОҙВІ) where groupArousal is inferred from socialSetting keywords ('crowd','cheering','silent','tense'). This explains introvert drain, mob psychology, why funerals feel heavy even without personal loss, and why mimicry increases liking. вҖ” Math: resonanceFactor = 1 + ОәВ·exp(вҲ’О”ПүВІ/2ОҙВІ). Оә = extraversionВ·agreeableness. О”Пү = |person.arousal вҲ’ inferredGroupArousal|. Оҙ = 0.25 (bandwidth). If groupArousal not inferable from context, Оә dampens to Оә/2.",
